{
  "doc_id": "32148",
  "text": "The partial atomic charges of all molecules were derived using the restrained electrostatic potential (RESP) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] charge-fitting procedure. The ab initio electrostatic potential for RESP was calculated using the GAUSSIAN 03 program at the HF/6-31G(d) level of theory. Preparation of all force field parameters was done by using the Antechamber module of the AMBER program package. The AMBER 2003 force field [24] parameter sets were used for all the solute and solvent molecules.",
